"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(DISTINCT Patient.ID)\nFROM Patient\nJOIN Laboratory ON Patient.ID = Laboratory.ID\nWHERE Laboratory.GPT < 60 AND Patient.SEX = 'M';\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of distinct male patients (`Patient.ID`) who have a normal glutamic pyruvic transaminase (GPT) level, which is defined as less than 60, according to the evidence provided. The query joins the `Patient` and `Laboratory` tables using the `ID` column, which is a foreign key relationship."